From behind bars, Nelson Mandela has dominated the fight for black rights in

South Africa.
In a short time, the ANC becomes the force behind black protests.
December, 1956 A campaign of civil disobedience by the ANC results in Mandela being detained along with 155 others and charged with treason.
July, 1963 With Mandela in jail, police raid ANC offices, seizing documents outlining guerrilla campaign.
July, 1988 Mandela turns 70.
August, 1988 Mandela contracts tuberculosis and is transferred to a hospital.
July, 1989 Mandela meets with outgoing president Botha at the presidential mansion.
February, 1990 De Klerk lifts ANC ban and says Mandela will be released.
